'''''Star Wars Insider'' 63''' is the sixty-third issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[November 5]], [[2002]]. This issue came packaged with an exclusive [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] card from [[Wizards of the Coast]]'s [[Star Wars Trading Card Game|''Star Wars'' Trading Card Game]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*From the Editor's Desk {{C|by Dave Gross}}
*[[Rebel Rumblings]]
*[[Star News]]: From the World of Lucasfilm {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]], [[Lisa Stevens]], and [[Mary Franklin]]}}
*[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]
*[[Behind the Magic]] &mdash; Dexter's Diner {{C|by [[Rob Coleman]]}}
*[[Gamescape]] &mdash; [[Star Wars: Bounty Hunter|A Fistful of Credits]]; [[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic|Balance of the Force]]; ''Star Wars'' Galaxies Update {{C|by [[Brett Rector]], [[Miguel Lopez]], and [[W. Haden Blackman]]}}
*[[Set Piece]] &mdash; Dagobah {{C|by [[Chris Trevas]] and [[Chris Reiff]]}}
*[[Bookshelf]] &mdash; Myth-Making: A Crew's-Eye View {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*[[Comics Link]] &mdash; Let Slip the Clones of War {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
*[[Scouting the Galaxy]] &mdash; All You Need to Know About 'All I Need to Know' {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]] &mdash; Twin Billing {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*[[The Last Page]] {{C|by [[Stan Shaw]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Dave Gross]]}}
*:<small>Is it too early to start talking about Episode III? Not for producer Rick McCallum.</small>
*"[[Inside Attack of the Clones|''Inside ''Attack of the Clones'']]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>Everything you need to know about berthing your ship in Mos Espa.</small>
*"[[Episode II DVD Preview]]" {{C|by Dave Gross & [[Michael Mikaelian]]}}
*:<small>The wait is over! Explore the great quality and bonus features you'll find only on the two-disc ''Attack of the Clones'' set.</small>
*"[[The Creatures of Episode II]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>A new breed of movie monster crashed onto the scene this summer. Read about their homeworlds, habits, and favorite snacks, plus behind-the-scenes factsand three furious arena matches!</small>
*"[[Dagobah to Death Star, Endor to Executor: A Short History of Elstree Studios|Dagobah to Death Star, Endor to ''Executor'': A Short History of Elstree Studios]]" {{C|by [[David Kaiser]]}}
*:<small>It took the will of the Force to turn Elstree Studios into one of the busiest soundstages in the world.</small>
*"[[Imperial Block Aid: The Largest & Smallest Star Wars LEGO Models to Date|Imperial Block Aid: The Largest & Smallest ''Star Wars'' LEGO Models to Date]]" {{C|by Michael Mikaelian}}
*:<small>The latest release for the ''Star Wars'' LEGO Ultimate Collectors' Series is not a local bulk-cruiser, mind you.</small>
*"[[Emissary of the Void]]": Episode V A Perilous Plan {{C|by [[Greg Keyes]]}}
*:<small>Rescue pilot Uldir Lochet, rogue Jedi Klin-Fa Gi, and the crew of ''No Luck Required'' risk everything to escape Yuuzhan Vong forces over Wayland.</small>
*"[[A New Hope Card Encyclopedia|''A New Hope'' Card Encyclopedia]]" {{C|by Michael Mikaelian}}
*:<small>See all 180 cards from Wizards of the Coast's third expansion for the ''Star Wars'' Trading Card Game based on the events of Episode IV.</small>

